@node "INSTALL" "SN MegaMail v1.0 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN MegaMail v1.0 - Installation Procedures
└────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Installation of SN PFiles is very simple!  Follow these easy steps and
enjoy the true power of CNet and ARexx today.

All SN PFiles are designed to use a common device ("SN:") assigned
to a directory or drive.  It is best when first setting up your SN:
assignment to assign it to a clean (unused) directory or drive.  (i.e.
create a directory in PFiles: called SN and assign SN: PFiles:SN.)
Also, be sure to add this assignment to your Startup-Sequence or
User-Startup so it's there when you reboot!  :)

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "SETUP" "SN MegaMail v1.0 - Setting Things Up
@toc "MAIN"
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN MegaMail v1.0 - Setting Things Up
└──────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  First of all, make sure you've done the SN: assignment as stated above
    in Installation Procedures.

 2  Place MegaMail in SN:.  (The SN: root, not in a directory.)

 3  Place MegaMail.hlp in systext:help/.  Make sure you rename it to
    just "MegaMail" once it gets there.

 4  Modify SysOp configurable variables in SN:MegaMail.

    a.  minaccs=10              /* Min Access Level to Use */
        maxleng=50              /* Max Lines (0 = User's Default) */
        edays=7                 /* Days to Expiration */
        expire=1                /* Expire?  0=NO, 1=YES, 2=USER */
        mfn="t:megamail."port   /* MegaMail Path/Filename */

    b.  Set minaccs to the lowest access level you want this utility
        to be usable by.  Set maxleng to the maximum number of lines
        you want allowed for a piece of MegaMail.  If you want it to
        go by the user's default maxline setting, put 0 here.  Ignore
        edays and expire for now.  They're not functional at this time.
        Set mfn to whatever you want.  I suggest just leaving it alone
        because it's just a temp file and will be deleted when done
        anyway.

 5  Make the following BBSMENU addition:

    Under either:  2; Available everywhere -or-
                   3; Main

        MEGA   |{#0SN:MegaMail}
    
    Or if you're only going to allow yourself to use it, put it under
    1; Maintenance menu.

 6  Add "MegaMail" to your main menu and write up a news file about it,
    so users will know of it's existence.

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
